Comparison of cases per 100,000 people¶

Back to top of page

In [12]:
metric = 'cases_100k'

fig, axes = plt.subplots(3,3, sharex=True, sharey=True, figsize=(10,12))
for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flatten()):
    ax.set_title(regions[i])
    ax.bar(covid[regions[i]][metric].index, covid[regions[i]][metric], alpha=.5)
    ax.plot(covid[regions[i]][metric+'_7m'].index, covid[regions[i]][metric+'_7m'],linewidth=2)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.DayLocator(bymonthday = 1))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%B'))
    ax.set_ylim(bottom=0)
fig.tight_layout(pad=3)
plt.show()
plt.close()
